==English==

===Noun===
'''a [[snowball]]’s [[chance]] in [[hell]]'''

#{{idiom}}, ''slang'' Little or no likelihood of occurrence or success.
#:''That small boat has '''a snowball’s chance in hell''' of surviving the hurricane.''

====Usage notes====
Often, the expression is used in the negative for even more emphasis.
:''That small boat '''doesn’t have a snowball’s chance in hell'''.''